attachments.title: LED-Lit Brain by djholt
attachments.text: A full-scale replica of a human brain (modeled from an anatomical MRI scan) mounted on a printable stand, featuring LED lights installed within each of the three supports. We want to see one printed using glow-in-the-dark filament. If you print one, send pictures. If you happen to have an MRI scanner handy, or want to participate in a study at your local university, then it might be easier than you think to print a replica of your own brain instead.
